--- Experiment 2 ---
Hypothesis: The angle blending on lines 99 and 106 uses linear interpolation of angles,
which is broken for angle wrapping. When heading≈+π and food≈-π (nearly same direction),
linear blend averages to ~0 (opposite direction!). Fix: use angular difference method
(compute delta via atan2(sin,cos), then add weighted delta). This should improve food
collection by eliminating wrong-way steering.
Changes: game.py steering logic — replace linear angle blending with proper angular interpolation.
