--- Experiment 3 ---
Hypothesis: Wall bouncing creates chaotic heading changes that waste movement. When the
creature hits a wall, its heading reflects abruptly, often away from food. Adding gentle
wall-avoidance steering when within 40px of walls should keep the creature navigating
smoothly in the food-rich interior and avoid wasted bounces. This is a code-level
improvement to game.py steering logic.
Changes: game.py — add wall avoidance steering force before turn rate clamping.
